OL,6,FWhile Trussell said it is difficult to
OL,7,Fmake precise comparisons between
OL,8,Fregions and UK nations, its research
OL,9,Fsuggested the North West of England
OL,10,Fhad the greatest food insecurity (26%
OL,11,Fof households), followed by the North
OL,12,FEast of England (23%), and Northern
OL,13,FIreland (21% of households).
OL,15,FYorkshire and Humberside had the
OL,16,Flowest food insecurity (10% of
OL,17,Fhouseholds) while for Wales and the
OL,18,FSouth East of England the proportion
OL,19,Fstood at 12% for each.
