OL,6,FIn Scotland, 15% of households were
OL,7,Fdeemed to be food insecure.
OL,9,FHelen Barnard, director of policy,
OL,10,Fresearch and impact at Trussell, said:
OL,11,F"Hunger and hardship are increasingly
OL,12,Fseen as a normal part of everyday life
OL,13,Fin the UK. This is not an inevitable
OL,14,Ftrend, but the result of systems that
OL,15,Furgently need updating ` particularly
OL,16,Four social security system.
